Method Detail

registerProvider

void registerProvider(AnubisProvider provider)
register a provider. This is a non-blocking operation. A provider should have a unique name in the system. Uniqueness is not currently tested by the locator. This could be changed to a blocking operation that does test uniqueness and passes or fails. It has not been decided how to deal with clashes when partitions merge.

deregisterProvider

void deregisterProvider(AnubisProvider provider)
deregister a provider - non-blocking.

registerListener

void registerListener(AnubisListener listener)
register a listener - this is a non-blocking method. It does not return a value, instead a notification will be provided to indicate the presence or absence of a provider. There is no guarantee that the registration call will return before the notification is given as the notification is asynchronous. If the partition is stable the notification will arrive with the usual timing guarantees, if not there are no guarantees.

deregisterListener

void deregisterListener(AnubisListener listener)
deregister a listener - non-blocking.

registerStability

void registerStability(AnubisStability stability)
registerStability registers an interface for stability notifications. This interface is called to inform the user when the local partition becomes stable or unstable.
